-- Uganda Hosts >1,800 Congolese Fleeing Govt, Rebels Fighting
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2013-07-25T14:10:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-25/uganda-hosts-1-800-congolese-fleeing-govt-rebels-fighting.html
Arrivals resulting from govt, M23
rebel clashes in North Kivu, are in addition to 67,000 refugees
who entered country earlier this month fleeing attacks by
another rebel group, Uganda Foreign Affairs Ministry says by e-mail from capital, Kampala.
* “A new emergency situation” building up in the southwestern
district of Kisoro, ministry says  To contact the reporter on this story:
